Title: Model of a Royal Statue
Description: This carved model depicts a standing male figure with long hair and a uraeus on his forehead. He has a pillar at back, and there are squares drawn on the pillar. His left leg and arm are broken off.
Provenance: Lambros [date and mode of acquisition unknown] (?); Dattari [date and mode of acquisition unknown] (?); Dikran Kelekian, New York and Paris [date and mode of acquisition unknown]; Henry Walters, Baltimore [date of acquisition unknown], by purchase; Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.
Creator: Egyptian
